Plug-in name: Pdg
Plug-in shortname: pdg
Description: Program Dependence Graph

Most options of the form '-pdg-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-pdg-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-fct-pdg <s>        build the dependence graph for the specified function
                    (preferably use -fct-pdg="")
-pdg                build the dependence graph of each function (opposite
                    option is -no-pdg)

*** DEBUG

-pdg-debug <n>      level of debug for plug-in Pdg (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-pdg-help           help of plug-in Pdg
-pdg-h              alias for option -pdg-help

*** OUTPUT

-codpds             show co-dependencies rather than dependencies (opposite
                    option is -no-codpds)
-pdg-dot <basename>  put the PDG of function <f> in basename.f.dot
                    (preferably use -pdg-dot="basename")

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-pdg-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from Pdg to a file. <K> is a
                    combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -pdg-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-pdg-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -pdg-msg-key help to get a list of
                    available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -pdg-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-pdg-verbose <n>    level of verbosity for plug-in Pdg (default to 1)
-pdg-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category <k1>
                    to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -pdg-warn-key help to get a
                    list of available categories, and * to enable all
                    categories. Possible statuses are inactive, feedback,
                    warning, error, abort, feedback-once, warning-once,
                    error-once. Defaults to warning. (preferably use
                    -pdg-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
